<subSubSection pageId="114" pageNumber="685" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="114.[1985,2571,2686,3103]" lastBlockId="114.[1368,2569,3109,3457]" pageId="114" pageNumber="685">
Urial taxonomy is controversial; formerly urial species: Ladakh (
<taxonomicName box="[2315,2443,2800,2829]" class="Mammalia" family="Bovidae" genus="Ovis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Artiodactyla" pageId="114" pageNumber="685" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="vignei">O. vignei</taxonomicName>
), Punjab (
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lydekker" authorityYear="1913" box="[1999,2214,2835,2868]" class="Mammalia" family="Bovidae" genus="Ovis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Artiodactyla" pageId="114" pageNumber="685" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="punjabiensis">O. punjabiensis</taxonomicName>
), Bukhara, and Afghan (
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hutton" authorityYear="1842" box="[1999,2155,2874,2907]" class="Mammalia" family="Bovidae" genus="Ovis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Artiodactyla" pageId="114" pageNumber="685" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="cycloceros">O. cycloceros</taxonomicName>
) recognized here, were usually classified as subspecies of 
<taxonomicName box="[2374,2526,2922,2947]" class="Mammalia" family="Bovidae" genus="Ovis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Artiodactyla" pageId="114" pageNumber="685" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="orientalis">O. orientalis</taxonomicName>
, or all as subspecies of 
<taxonomicName box="[2271,2389,2952,2985]" class="Mammalia" family="Bovidae" genus="Ovis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Artiodactyla" pageId="114" pageNumber="685" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="vignei">O. vignei</taxonomicName>
. (The name 
<taxonomicName box="[1987,2101,2992,3025]" class="Mammalia" family="Bovidae" genus="Ovis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Artiodactyla" pageId="114" pageNumber="685" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="orientalis">orientalis</taxonomicName>
is based on a hybrid population in north-central 
<collectingCountry box="[2226,2282,3036,3065]" name="Iran" pageId="114" pageNumber="685">Iran</collectingCountry>
and is not usable.) This species is in need of distributional, anatomical, karyological, and molecular genetics studies to define its distribution and relationship to other urial species. Monotypic.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
